.TH DDC-SLIDER 1 "__VERSION__" "ddc-slider" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ddc-slider \- DDC/CI brightness and contrast control for monitors
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ddc-slider
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ddc-slider
is a GTK3 application that controls monitor brightness and contrast via the
DDC/CI protocol using
.BR ddcutil (1).
It runs as a system tray icon by default, or as a standalone floating window.
.PP
Features include per-monitor brightness and contrast sliders, a master slider
for multi-monitor setups, color temperature presets via
.BR redshift (1),
configurable user presets, and a state cache for instant startup.
.PP
On first launch, \fBddc-slider\fR probes for DDC-capable monitors using
\fBddcutil detect\fR and caches the result. Subsequent launches use the cache
for instant startup and refresh values from hardware in the background.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-b, \-\-bus \fINUM\fR
Use a specific I2C bus number instead of auto-detection.
.TP
.B \-\-standalone
Show as a floating window instead of a system tray icon.
.TP
.B \-\-get
Print current brightness of the first monitor and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-set \fIVALUE\fR
Set brightness of the first monitor to VALUE (0\-100) and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-get\-contrast
Print current contrast of the first monitor and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-set\-contrast \fIVALUE\fR
Set contrast of the first monitor to VALUE (0\-100) and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-min \fIVALUE\fR
Minimum slider value (default: 0).
.TP
.B \-\-max \fIVALUE\fR
Maximum slider value (default: 100).
.TP
.B \-\-step \fIVALUE\fR
Slider step size (default: 5).
.TP
.B \-\-scroll\-step \fIVALUE\fR
Scroll wheel step size for the tray icon (default: 1).
.TP
.B \-\-config \fIFILE\fR
Path to a JSON config file with presets. Default:
.IR ~/.config/ddc-slider/config.json .
.TP
.B \-\-no\-config
Disable config file loading.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-cache
Skip the state cache and force a fresh hardware probe.
.TP
.B \-\-icon \fISTYLE\fR
Tray icon color: \fBlight\fR (white icon), \fBdark\fR (black icon),
or \fBauto\fR (detect from GTK theme, default). Icons are stored as
SVGs in \fI~/.config/ddc-slider/icons/\fR and can be replaced with
custom icons.
.TP
.B \-v, \-V, \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.SH TRAY ICON USAGE
.TP
.B Left-click
Toggle the brightness/contrast popup.
.TP
.B Scroll wheel
Adjust brightness of all monitors.
.TP
.B Right-click
Context menu with presets, redshift toggle, and quit.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The config file at \fI~/.config/ddc-slider/config.json\fR supports:
.PP
.nf
{
  "scroll_step": 1,
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "Movie",
      "brightness": 30,
      "contrast": 60,
      "color_temp": 3500
    }
  ],
  "monitor_names": {
    "3": "Philips",
    "9": "Dell right"
  }
}
.fi
.PP
The \fBmonitor_names\fR section maps I2C bus numbers to custom display names.
Find bus numbers with \fBddcutil detect\fR. If not set, the EDID model name
is used (e.g. "PHL 275E1").
.PP
Color temperature presets require
.BR redshift (1)
to be installed.
.SH STATE CACHE
Monitor detection results and last-used slider values are cached at
\fI~/.config/ddc-slider/state.json\fR to allow instant startup. The cache
expires after 24 hours. Use \fB\-\-no\-cache\fR to force a fresh probe.
.SH SETUP
.TP
.B 1. Install ddcutil
pacman \-S ddcutil
.TP
.B 2. Load the i2c\-dev kernel module
sudo modprobe i2c\-dev
.TP
.B 3. Add your user to the i2c group
sudo usermod \-aG i2c $USER
.PP
Log out and back in for group changes to take effect.
.TP
.B 4. Verify access
ddcutil detect
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/ddc-slider/config.json
User configuration with presets and scroll step.
.TP
.I ~/.config/ddc-slider/state.json
Cached monitor state for instant startup.
.TP
.I ~/.config/ddc-slider/icons/
Auto-generated SVG tray icons (brightness-light.svg, brightness-dark.svg).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error (no monitors found, ddcutil failure, etc.)
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ddcutil (1),
.BR redshift (1),
.BR i2c\-dev (4)
